# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Eval run output (regenerated each run) — Phase A panel runs + Phase B
# per-brand runs both land at <repo>/tests/reports/runs/<ts>(-phase-a)/.
# Latest-pointer files (latest.md / latest-phase-a.md) are also regenerated.
tests/reports/runs/
tests/reports/visual-check/
tests/reports/latest*.md

# Sample workspace artifacts that are large + regenerable
# (keep brand.json + pages.txt + assets/ — they're the LLM/quality-gate output)
samples/*/recon/
samples/*/raw-assets.json
samples/*/eval-output/

# Phase 1 transient workspace — should live in OS tempdir (init_workspace.py)
# but gitignore the in-project locations too as defense in depth
.web-to-ds-workspace/
.deckify-workspace/

# skill-creator workspace — sibling to a skill dir, holds per-iteration eval
# outputs (baseline.json, with_skill/, without_skill/, benchmark.json, etc).
# Path convention from the skill-creator skill is `<skill-dir>-workspace/`.
skills/*-workspace/
*-workspace/iteration-*/

# Local backups (user-managed, not part of the skill)
decks/backup/

# Editor scratch
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~

# Claude Code session state
.claude/

# Maintainer-local agent rules — kept on disk for the maintainer's own
# AI-assisted workflow inside this repo, but never committed. Each
# contributor can keep their own personal version (or none). The shipped
# project documentation lives in README.md / TESTING.md / SKILL.md.
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md

# === Launch / promo artifacts ===
# Most of /assets/social/launch/ is local working files: video build pipeline
# (Remotion source + node_modules + ffmpeg scratch), recon screenshots,
# editorial drafts. The shipped artifacts (the final video + the README's
# referenced images) are the only thing that needs to live in git.

# Entire Remotion video build pipeline lives locally — source code, build
# artefacts, rendered MP4. The MP4 itself is uploaded to GitHub user-attachments
# CDN (see README), not committed to the repo.
assets/social/launch/v3-remotion/

# Reconnaissance screenshots — regenerable from agent-browser, large
assets/social/launch/tiffany-recon/

# Background music — Pixabay royalty-free, regenerable, large
assets/social/launch/audio/

# Editorial drafts + viewpoint cards — local working copies, not part of
# the public skill (used as input to social media posts, not to the repo).
assets/social/launch/wechat.md
assets/social/launch/xiaohongshu.md
assets/social/launch/video-script.md
assets/social/launch/Seacen的写作风格.md
assets/social/launch/wechat-images/
assets/social/launch/cards/

# Raw deck screenshots used as source for showcase/ images. The curated
# subset already lives under assets/showcase/; the full pool stays local
# (18 MB, regenerable from `decks/<brand>/<brand>-deck.html` via screenshot).
assets/social/raw/
